Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the sweet potato to a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{20-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pour 300ml cold salted @water{to taste} into a medium #pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%grams} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for ~{12%minutes}.

Remove the pot from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Use a teaspoon to easily scrape away the peel.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%grams} (stalks and all).

Halve the @chilli{1}(halved, core and seeds discarded). Finely chop.

Halve the @baby corn{150%grams} lengthways.

Zest and quarter the @lime{1}.

When the sweet potato has 10 mins of cooking time to go, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the baby corn and stir-fry for ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the @thai style spice mix{1%sachet}, ginger and chilli (use less if you don't like spice) and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Pop in the @red Thai style paste{1%sachet}, @coconut milk{1%pack} and 50ml water (double for 4p). Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the roasted sweet potato through the curry.

Add a squeeze of lime juice.

Stir in a splash of water if the curry is too thick.

Season to taste with salt, pepper and more lime juice if desired.

Mix the lime zest into the rice, fluffing it up as you go.

Serve the rice in #bowls{} and top with the sweet potato curry.

Finish with a sprinkling of coriander.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.